# .mailmap — normalize author/committer identities in git log/shortlog and on
# GitHub commit views. Does not rewrite history; git renders the canonical
# form on the left when it sees any of the aliases on the right.
#
# Format: Canonical Name <canonical@email> <alias@email>
#         Canonical Name <canonical@email> Alias Name <alias@email>
#
# See git-shortlog(1) "MAPPING AUTHORS" for the full precedence rules.

# Fix stray curly-quote in name that made commits render as `"Jim <jim@jk.digital>`.
Jim Kennedy <jim@jk.digital> “Jim <jim@jk.digital>

# Fold the older personal email into the canonical jk.digital identity.
Jim Kennedy <jim@jk.digital> JimAKennedy <the.jim.kennedy@gmail.com>
Jim Kennedy <jim@jk.digital> Jim Kennedy <the.jim.kennedy@gmail.com>
